Tomorrow marks the 20th anniversary of her death, for which Saldívar is serving life for.

Lopez, who actually went on to play Selena in a 1997 biopic, added that the young artist was 'special' and 'moved the world in a different way.'

She continued: 'That's why we're still talking about her 20 years later.... People like that don't come along every day. 

'There is never going to be another Selena.'

Just two years after playing Selena, Lopez successfully managed to convert herself from a film star to a pop star.

